# UI Design System

**Source of truth:** `src/App.jsx` (mock) — primitives migrate to `src/ui/` as stories extract slices

Full catalog: `docs/design/ui-reference.md`  
Application docs: `docs/prototype/README.md` (slice-first workflow)

## Before building UI

1. Read primitives in `src/App.jsx` (or `src/ui/` once extracted).
2. Reuse them — do not invent parallel button/card/color systems.
3. Match layout: mobile-first, `max-w-[430px]`, horizontal padding `px-5` (20px), bottom safe area `h-[100px]` on tab screens.
4. **Slice first** — extract the story's UI from `App.jsx` before wiring backends.

## Styling approach

**Tailwind CSS v4** with theme tokens in `src/index.css` (`@theme`). Use utility classes — not inline `style` objects — except for dynamic values (progress bar width, accent borders from `COLORS`).

## Color tokens

### Tailwind classes (preferred)

| Class | Use |
|-------|-----|
| `coach-bg` | App background |
| `coach-surface` | Tab bar, modals |
| `coach-card` | Cards, inputs |
| `coach-border` | Borders and dividers |
| `coach-orange`, `coach-orange-light`, `coach-orange-glow` | Brand / primary actions / active tab |
| `coach-green` | Success / owned / positive |
| `coach-blue` | Info / player accents |
| `coach-purple` | AI / secondary accent |
| `coach-yellow` | Warning / trial |
| `coach-red` | Error / sign out |
| `coach-t1`, `coach-t2`, `coach-t3` | Primary, secondary, muted text |

### `COLORS` object (dynamic inline styles)

Defined in `App.jsx` for progress bars, left-border accents, and gradient overlays. Mirror values in `src/index.css` `@theme` — never hardcode duplicate hex elsewhere.

Helpers `tcx()`, `bgcx()`, `bdcx()` map `COLORS.*` hex values to Tailwind text/bg/border classes.

## Typography

| Token | Font | Tailwind | Use |
|-------|------|----------|-----|
| Display | Oswald | `font-display` | Headings, buttons, stats, screen titles |
| Body | DM Sans | `font-body` | Labels, body text, inputs, tab labels |
| Mono | JetBrains Mono | `font-mono` | Percentages, numeric stats |

Fonts load via Google Fonts in `App.jsx` `useEffect`; theme aliases live in `src/index.css`. `main.jsx` also loads `@fontsource/dm-sans` as a fallback.

Screen titles: `PageHeader` — `font-display text-[26px] font-bold text-coach-t1`  
Section headers: `font-display text-base font-semibold uppercase text-coach-t1`

## Primitives — use these, don't recreate

| Component | When to use |
|-----------|-------------|
| `PageHeader` | Screen header with title, optional subtitle, back, settings, trial badge |
| `Card` | Card container (`onClick` for pressable rows) |
| `Btn` | Actions (`primary` = orange fill; default = orange glow) |
| `Badge` | Status / tier / tag labels |
| `Field` | Labeled form input |
| `TrialBanner` | Trial countdown CTA on home |
| `PaywallModal` | Tier-gated feature overlay |
| `DashedBtn` | "+ Add …" dashed-border actions |
| `PackageThumb` | Store package image with gradient overlay |
| `Icon*` | SVG icons (`IconHome`, `IconBack`, `IconLock`, etc.) |

## Patterns

- App shell: `max-w-[430px] bg-coach-bg font-body text-coach-t1`
- Primary CTA: `<Btn primary full>`
- List rows: `<Card onClick={...} className="flex items-center gap-3.5">`
- Filter chips: `rounded-full` pills — selected: `border-coach-orange bg-coach-orange-glow text-coach-orange`
- Segmented tabs: `rounded-xl bg-coach-card p-1` with active segment `bg-coach-orange text-white`
- Inputs: `rounded-[10px] border border-coach-border bg-coach-card font-body text-coach-t1`
- Progress bars: `h-1.5 rounded-sm bg-coach-border` + inner div with `width` and `backgroundColor` from `COLORS`
- Left accent cards: `border-l-[3px]` with `borderLeftColor` or `border-l-coach-orange`
- Tier gating: `canAccess(user, feature)` + `tryA(feature, action)` + `PaywallModal`
- Touch targets: `min-h-11` / `h-12` for icon buttons

## Do not

- Hardcode hex colors that duplicate `coach-*` tokens or `COLORS`
- Use colors from `App.css` (Vite boilerplate — not the app theme)
- Create new one-off `<button>` or card styles when `Btn` / `Card` suffice
- Reintroduce the legacy inline-style `C` token object or old component names (`Cd`, `Hero`, `Pill`, `I`)

## Extraction (when refactoring)

When a story grows a feature, keep shared UI in `src/ui/` — move existing primitives unchanged; do not redesign during extraction.
